Description: The determination of how the injury or disease lead to death
Valid Values: accident, homicide, natural causes, suicide, undetermined

Description: Cause of death attributable to unforeseen or unplanned circumstances
Cause of death attributable to the actions of another person
Cause of death attributable to the progression of a disease or pre-existing condition, and not attributable to any outside action or force
Cause of death attributable to intentionally inflicted self harm
Cause of death cannot be determined
